ionary communications technologies in their business systems and transformed patterns of development through their innovative advances, the book challenges simplified representations of the contemporary economy as historically unprecedented. Territories of Profit also incorporates information from interview sources within Dell to portray the "Dell Model" in ways never before revealed in existing studies of the PC maker.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Corporate & Business History.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362403040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503624030423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503624030/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles